Version 2.6.7 [26 Feb 2015]
---------------------------
- Fix bug in t2t_docsys_html_addlevel.conf.
- Further differences against txt2tags version 2.6:
  - Check that all title anchors are unique.


Version 2.6.6 [12 Jan 2015]
---------------------------
- Use lowercase version of utf-8 encoding name.


Version 2.6.5 [12 Jan 2015]
---------------------------
- Fix bug introduced in 2.6.4 in HTML and TeX generation.


Version 2.6.4 [12 Jan 2015]
---------------------------
- Further differences against txt2tags version 2.6:
  - Support python3.
  - Make utf-8 encoding default.


Version 2.6.3 [10 Jan 2015]
---------------------------
- Document t2t_docsys using itself.
- Further differences against txt2tags version 2.6:
  - Two or more spaces at end of line denote line break.


Version 2.6.2 [9 Jan 2015]
--------------------------
- Use uppercase for Makefile variables.
- Further differences against txt2tags version 2.6:
  - Add simple GitHub Flavoured Markdown support.


Version 2.6.1 [8 Jan 2015]
--------------------------
- Further differences against txt2tags version 2.6:
  - Remove spaces at end of line.
  - Honour empty/nonempty line between para/list and para/verb.
  - html: Use lowercase and HTML5 friendly tags.


Version 2.6.0 [7 Jan 2015]
--------------------------
- Initial public release.
- Differences against txt2tags version 2.6:
  - txt: Reflow paragraphs to 80 columns.
  - txt: Do not use tabs to indicate heading level.
  - txt: Use = for top-level headings and - otherwise.
  - txt: Remove superfluous empty lines.
  - pdf: Use lstlisting instead of verbatim, which allows
         automatic line breaking and hyperlinks in verbatim.
  - pdf: Add linebreak after a definition item.
  - html,pdf: Ignore =* in headings.
